sity. We suggest that the observed\nvariance in RRM and the anti-correlation of RRM with p both require a\npopulation of magnetized intervening objects that lie outside the Milky Way but\nin the foreground to the emitting sources.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Sep 2012 02:29:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 12 Oct 2012 15:19:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 8 May 2013 12:41:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-02"}
